%N A394394 Largest number of distinct lines determined by pairs of cell centers of a polycube with n cells.
%H A394394 Pontus von Brömssen, <a href="/A393939/a393939.gif">Illustration of the unique free polycube with 26 cells and no 3 collinear cells</a>.
%H A394394 <a href="/index/Pol#polyominoes">Index entries for sequences related to polyominoes</a>.
%F A394394 a(n+1)-n <= a(n) <= n*(n-1)/2, with equality in the second part if and only if n <= 26 = largest k such that A393938(k,2) > 0. The first part is equivalent to n*(n-1)/2 - a(n) being nondecreasing.
